Good to see ya.

01:11:57.582 --> 01:11:58.115
DICAPRIO: Thank you so much.
PRES. OBAMA: You doing alright?

01:11:58.148 --> 01:11:58.783
DICAPRIO: Absolutely.

01:11:58.816 --> 01:11:59.984
PRES. OBAMA: Alright. C'mon.

01:12:00.017 --> 01:12:03.654
The Paris Agreement ended up
being a historic agreement,

01:12:03.688 --> 01:12:07.292
not because it gets us to where
we need to be eventually,

01:12:07.325 --> 01:12:12.430
but for the first time, locking
in all countries into verifiable

01:12:12.463 --> 01:12:14.665
steps and targets that
they're gonna take.

01:12:14.699 --> 01:12:17.702
It creates the architecture
that allows us to finally start

01:12:17.735 --> 01:12:19.370
dealing with this
problem in a serious way.

01:12:19.404 --> 01:12:20.605
DICAPRIO: So you were
happy with what came of it?

01:12:20.638 --> 01:12:23.341
PRES. OBAMA: I, I, I was happy
that we put the architecture

01:12:23.374 --> 01:12:25.210
in place.

01:12:25.243 --> 01:12:27.645
The, the targets that have been
set in Paris are nowhere near

01:12:27.678 --> 01:12:31.649
enough for what the scientists
tell us we have to do eventually

01:12:31.682 --> 01:12:33.451
to solve this problem.

01:12:33.484 --> 01:12:37.054
But if we can use the next
20 years to apply existing

01:12:37.087 --> 01:12:40.225
technologies to reduce
carbon emissions,

01:12:40.258 --> 01:12:44.395
and then start slowly turning up
the dials as new technologies

01:12:44.429 --> 01:12:47.131
come on line, so that we have
more and more ambitious targets

01:12:47.164 --> 01:12:51.769
each year, then, we're not gonna
completely reverse the warming

01:12:51.802 --> 01:12:55.139
that now is inevitable, but we
can stop it before it becomes

01:12:55.173 --> 01:12:56.574
catastrophic.

01:12:56.607 --> 01:12:58.543
DICAPRIO: And it's no secret
that you've been under great

01:12:58.576 --> 01:13:02.146
opposition to try to implement
some of your climate change

01:13:02.180 --> 01:13:03.381
initiatives. And.

01:13:03.414 --> 01:13:05.850
PRES. OBAMA: We've got some
folks on the other side. Yeah.

01:13:05.883 --> 01:13:08.519
DICAPRIO: So someone that comes
into office that does not

01:13:08.553 --> 01:13:11.356
believe in the science
of climate change,

01:13:11.389 --> 01:13:14.392
do they have the capacity
and the power to dismantle

01:13:14.425 --> 01:13:16.126
everything that you've
already worked for?

01:13:16.160 --> 01:13:19.364
PRES. OBAMA: Even if somebody
came in, campaigning on denying

01:13:19.397 --> 01:13:24.869
climate science, reality has
a way of, you know,

01:13:24.902 --> 01:13:27.805
hitting you in the nose if
you're not paying attention.

01:13:27.838 --> 01:13:32.610
And I think that the public is
starting to realize the science,

01:13:32.643 --> 01:13:34.917
in part because
it's indisputable.

01:13:35.780 --> 01:13:38.549
DICAPRIO: I, I
admire your optimism.

01:13:38.583 --> 01:13:39.350
PRES. OBAMA: Yeah.
DICAPRIO: But

01:13:39.384 --> 01:13:41.286
you start to look at
the science,

01:13:41.319 --> 01:13:43.188
look at what's going on
in the Antarctic and,

01:13:43.221 --> 01:13:46.123
and scientists saying that
there are sections of ice that

01:13:46.156 --> 01:13:49.594
guarantee four to six
meters of ocean level rise,

01:13:49.627 --> 01:13:52.897
which will be catastrophic
for the future.

01:13:52.930 --> 01:13:56.133
You are the leader
of the Free World.

01:13:56.166 --> 01:13:59.437
You have access to information
that most people do not.

01:13:59.470 --> 01:14:03.841
What makes you terrified
for the future?

01:14:03.874 --> 01:14:07.512
PRES. OBAMA: Uh, a huge portion
of the world's population

01:14:07.545 --> 01:14:09.714
lives near oceans.
DICAPRIO: Mhm.

01:14:09.747 --> 01:14:16.387
PRES. OBAMA: If they start
moving, then you start seeing,

01:14:16.421 --> 01:14:18.889
um, scarce resources.

01:14:18.923 --> 01:14:21.826
The subject of competition
between populations.

01:14:21.859 --> 01:14:24.395
This is the reason why
the Pentagon has said,

01:14:24.429 --> 01:14:26.197
this is a national
security issue.

01:14:26.231 --> 01:14:28.165
This isn't just an
environmental issue.

01:14:28.199 --> 01:14:30.468
This is a national
security issue.

01:14:30.501 --> 01:14:36.374
You know, in addition to just
the sadness that I would feel if

01:14:36.407 --> 01:14:40.545
my kids can never see a glacier,
the way I saw when I went up

01:14:40.578 --> 01:14:43.648
to Alaska, uh, you know,
that's the romantic side of it.

01:14:43.681 --> 01:14:46.517
That's the side that takes
a walk with my daughters

01:14:46.551 --> 01:14:49.320
and I wanna be able to, them
to see, or my grandkids,

01:14:49.354 --> 01:14:50.788
I want them to see the
same things as I saw

01:14:50.821 --> 01:14:51.956
as I was growing up.

01:14:51.989 --> 01:14:55.760
Even if you were
unsentimental about that,

01:14:55.793 --> 01:14:58.863
in very hard‐headed terms,
you've gotta worry about

01:14:58.896 --> 01:15:00.731
the national security
implications of this,

01:15:00.765 --> 01:15:04.935
and the capacity for the
existing world order

01:15:04.969 --> 01:15:07.938
as we understand it to
survive the kinds of strains

01:15:07.972 --> 01:15:10.375
that the scientists are
predicting without action.

01:15:10.408 --> 01:15:14.345
This is why we have
to take action now.

01:15:14.379 --> 01:15:17.515
If we keep pushing keep prodding
and most importantly keep

01:15:17.548 --> 01:15:21.352
educating the public
there's no reason why, uh,

01:15:21.386 --> 01:15:24.255
we can't solve this
problem in time.

01:15:24.289 --> 01:15:25.390
DICAPRIO: Thank you for
your time, Mr. President.

01:15:25.423 --> 01:15:26.291
PRES. OBAMA: You bet.

01:15:26.324 --> 01:15:27.492
Thanks for the good
work you're doing.

01:15:27.525 --> 01:15:28.693
DICAPRIO: Thank you so much.
PRES. OBAMA: Alright. Good?

